y carry `tool_use_id`; the tool name is on the earlier `tool_use`. So if we want `tool_name` on results, the parser needs a tiny `tool_use_id -> tool_name` map while reading the file. That feels worth it and still POC-sized.\n\nThis also exposes a current weakness: our Claude parser would treat many tool results as generic `user` records with no `text` and no `tool_name`. So the normalized shape is not just prettier, it would make Claude records genuinely usable without re-parsing `source_record`.\n\nI’d slightly revise the schema from the previous message:\n\n- `kind`: `message | tool_call | tool_result | session | other`\n- `source_event_kind`: provider-specific, like `codex:response_item:function_call` or `claude:assistant:tool_use`\n- `text`: normalized human-readable message/result text\n- `tool_input`: redacted JSON value, not just a string, because Claude has object inputs and Codex has JSON-string arguments\n- `source_record`: redacted provenance, possibly pruned later\n\nThat feels like the right common shape for both Codex and Claude.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T10:56:29.969Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}